  localization ring homomorphism \(R\to R_f\).  There is a canonical
  \(R_f\)-linear map
  \[
    \eta_M:\;M_f\;\longrightarrow\;
    \Gamma\bigl(\operatorname{Spec}R_f,\;q_f^{*}\widetilde M\bigr)
  \]
  into the global sections over \(\operatorname{Spec}R_f\) of the inverse image
  \(q_f^{*}\widetilde M\) (\cref{mathlib:scheme_modules_pullback}).  Here
  \(M_f:=R_f\otimes_R M\) is the extension-of-scalars module along \(R\to R_f\)
  (\cref{mathlib:extendRestrictScalarsAdj}), and \(\eta_M\) is the adjunction transpose
  of the \(R\to R_f\)-semilinear comparison map (\cref{mathlib:semilinearMapAddEquiv}).
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  \leanok
  \uses{mathlib:pullbackPushforwardAdjunction, mathlib:scheme_modules_pullback, mathlib:oxmod_pushforward, mathlib:tilde, mathlib:tilde_isoTop, mathlib:extendRestrictScalarsAdj, mathlib:semilinearMapAddEquiv, found:pushforward_smul_coherence}
  The unit of the adjunction \(q_f^{*}\dashv (q_f)_{*}\)
  (\cref{mathlib:pullbackPushforwardAdjunction}) at \(\widetilde M\) is a morphism
  of \(\cO_{\operatorname{Spec}R}\)-modules
  \(\widetilde M\to (q_f)_{*}\,q_f^{*}\widetilde M\)
  (\cref{mathlib:oxmod_pushforward}).  Taking global sections over
  \(\operatorname{Spec}R\) and using that the global sections of a pushforward
  over the whole base are the sections over the source's top open,
  \(\Gamma(\operatorname{Spec}R,(q_f)_{*}\mathcal G)=
  \Gamma(\operatorname{Spec}R_f,\mathcal G)\), together with the top-sections
  identification \(\Gamma(\operatorname{Spec}R,\widetilde M)=M\)
  (\cref{mathlib:tilde_isoTop}), produces a canonical \(R\)-linear map
  \(M\to\Gamma(\operatorname{Spec}R_f,q_f^{*}\widetilde M)\).  The target carries a
  native \(R_f\)-action (sections over \(\operatorname{Spec}R_f\)); by scalar
  coherence (\cref{found:pushforward_smul_coherence}) this \(R\)-linear map is exactly
  the restriction-of-scalars of an \(R\to R_f\)-semilinear comparison
  (\cref{mathlib:semilinearMapAddEquiv}).  Transposing it across the
  extension--restriction-of-scalars adjunction
  \(R_f\otimes_R(-)\dashv\) restriction (\cref{mathlib:extendRestrictScalarsAdj})
  yields the \(R_f\)-linear map
  \(\eta_M:M_f\to\Gamma(\operatorname{Spec}R_f,q_f^{*}\widetilde M)\), where
  \(M_f=R_f\otimes_R M\) is the extension-of-scalars object.
\end{proof}

