  \uses{mathlib:scheme_modules_pullback, mathlib:toPresheaf_sheafification_unit, mathlib:stalkFunctor_unit_toSheafify_isIso, def:peer_module_iso_locality}
  For the localization Spec map \(q_f:\operatorname{Spec}R_f\to\operatorname{Spec}R\) and
  \(x\in\operatorname{Spec}R_f\), the sheaf-of-modules pullback \(q_f^{*}\widetilde M\)
  (\cref{mathlib:scheme_modules_pullback}) is the sheafification of the presheaf-of-modules
  pullback of \(\widetilde M\), and the sheafification unit induces an isomorphism on stalks:
  \((q_f^{*}\widetilde M)_x\cong(\,\text{presheaf-pullback of }\widetilde M\,)_x\).
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  \leanok
  \uses{mathlib:scheme_modules_pullback, mathlib:toPresheaf_sheafification_unit, mathlib:stalkFunctor_unit_toSheafify_isIso, def:peer_module_iso_locality}
  By the stalk-local criterion for module isomorphisms
  (\cref{def:peer_module_iso_locality}) the comparison is reduced to its effect on the
  underlying \(\mathrm{Ab}\)-valued sheaves, i.e. it suffices to show that the stalk functor
  on abelian-group sheaves sends it to an isomorphism.  The sheaf-of-modules
  pullback is the sheafification of the presheaf-of-modules pullback
  (\cref{mathlib:scheme_modules_pullback}), and the comparison map between them is the
  sheafification-adjunction unit.  Its underlying-\(\mathrm{Ab}\) presheaf map is exactly the
  abelian-group sheafification unit of the underlying presheaf of the
  presheaf pullback (\cref{mathlib:toPresheaf_sheafification_unit}).  Finally the stalk
  functor at \(x\) sends the sheafification unit to an isomorphism
  (\cref{mathlib:stalkFunctor_unit_toSheafify_isIso}, applied with value category
  \(\mathcal C=\mathrm{Ab}\)).  Hence the stalk of \(q_f^{*}\widetilde M\) at \(x\) is
  canonically isomorphic to the stalk of the presheaf pullback at \(x\).
\end{proof}

